{"title":"fix(remediation): increase mem-load memory limit to prevent OOMKilled","body":"Root cause: The mem-load container's memory limit (32Mi) is insufficient for the stress command which attempts to allocate 50M of VM memory, causing repeated OOMKilled restarts.

Evidence: Back-off restarting failed container mem-load in pod vigil-app-5fc67bd7bf-hszdx_default(f4c50b3d-013a-48a0-9f92-9efca4e98cf9)

Fix: Increased mem-load memory limit from 32Mi to 64Mi in Deployment/vigil-app."}
